cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and sequence-to-sequence models. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it proposes a new attention mechanism for neural networks. Additionally, it may be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of neural networks, and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as attention mechanisms are commonly used in image processing tasks.
